The paper proposes a new framework for reinforcement learning with a focus on safety, which is a common concern in the field of machine learning. The paper also discusses policy-gradient theorem and temporal difference errors, which are key concepts in the sub-fields of machine learning and robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed algorithm in various environments, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
